ZH: 这位老师很擅长用明确的问题来诱导学生思考。
EN: This teacher is good at using specific questions to induce students to think.

ZH: 电影的镜头设计是为了诱导观众的情绪。
EN: The cinematography of the movie was designed to induce the audience's emotions.

ZH: 这个广告诱导消费者购买了更多的产品。
EN: This advertisement induced consumers to purchase more products.

ZH: 随着人们生活水平的提高，有些社交平台诱导人们纷纷展示奢华生活。
EN: As people's living standards improve, some social platforms induce people to show off their luxurious lifestyles.

ZH: 校园欺凌会诱导受害者产生心理问题。
EN: Bullying on campus can induce psychological problems in victims.

ZH: 该公司的广告宣传是否诱导了顾客的误导行为？
EN: Did the company's advertising campaign induce misleading behavior from customers?

ZH: 他太容易被人诱导了。
EN: He is easily induced by others.

ZH: 孩子被朋友诱导去做一些不好的事情。
EN: The child was induced by his friends to do some bad things.

ZH: 长时间的任劳任怨容易诱导出抑郁症。
EN: Long-term hard work can easily induce depression.

ZH: 诱导过度妄想会导致精神紊乱。
EN: Inducing excessive delusions can cause mental disorders.

ZH: 这个预言诱导人们接受了不真实的信息。
EN: This prophecy induced people to accept unreal information.

ZH: 过度的竞争诱导商家降低产品的质量。
EN: Excessive competition induces businesses to lower the quality of their products.

ZH: 这则消息诱导了证券市场的不稳定。
EN: This news induced instability in the stock market.

ZH: 人们担心政治宣传会诱导公民对某一方选择。
EN: People worry that political propaganda will induce citizens to choose a certain side.

ZH: 我们应该警惕那些试图诱导我们做出错误决策的人。
EN: We should be wary of those who try to induce us to make wrong decisions.

ZH: 公司利用恶意邮件诱导员工泄露机密信息。
EN: The company uses malicious emails to induce employees to disclose confidential information.

ZH: 别被一时冲动诱导了你的行动。
EN: Don't let your actions be induced by momentary impulse.

ZH: 广告具有诱导消费的作用。
EN: Advertisements have the effect of inducing consumption.

ZH: 同龄人常常诱导年轻人追求时尚。
EN: Peers often induce young people to pursue fashion.

ZH: 这位演讲者成功地诱导了观众的注意力。
EN: The speaker successfully induced the audience's attention.
